issue.title: The edge menu should be closed when selection menu is open
issue.body:
![obrazek](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/75206927-8162-4928-bf44-95340c62194d)

On a side note: When only edges are selected and no class is selected, then the menu should be different and opened on the lastly selected edge.

comment.body:
The part about edge menu closing was implemented

> On a side note: When only edges are selected and no class is selected, then the menu should be different and opened on the lastly selected edge.

Unfortunately didn't have time to implement this. And since the rendering of edge toolbars is different than for nodes, the implementation wasn't as straightforward, so I didn't want to implement something half-baked, just for @skodapetr to have it rewrite couple of months later

performed_via_github_app.description: PRMerger partially automates PR review and issue management in Learn content repositories. Depending on the scope of proposed changes, PRs are either merged automatically or queued for human review. Issues are assigned a default priority based on page views and labeled with appropriate content areas. PRMerger also provides a set of hashtag commands to allow users with Read permissions to perform Write-level actions on PRs and issues.
